16/11/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) President Milan Jelic on Wednesday (November 15th) gave the mandate for forming the new entity government to Milorad Dodik, prime minister and leader of the Alliance of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), which won the recent parliamentary elections. SNSD already has agreed to form an entity-level coalition with the Democratic People's Alliance and Socialist Party. According to Dodik, negotiations continue with the Party for Democratic Progress. 
Also Wednesday, High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling met with Jelic and a number of other senior RS officials in an attempt to reach agreement on sensitive issues, including co-operation to the UN war crimes tribunal, possible constitutional changes, and the special relations accord between RS and Serbia. Schwarz-Schilling said he would play a leading role in reforming the constitution. (Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 16/11/06; Fena, RTRS, Fonet - 15/11/06)
